<raw><![CDATA[ SYDNEY, Feb 11 (Reuters) - Rio Tinto   CEOTom Albanese said on Thursday the Anglo-Australian miner maycontinue to defer big modernisation of aluminium projects untilit sees an upturn in OECD economies. Rio echoed rival BHP Billiton's  caution in callinga global recovery on Thursday and cut its 2009 dividend afterreporting its worst second-half profit in three years. (Reporting by Michael Perry; Editing by Mark Bendeich)             ]]></raw>
